<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-06T14:32:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-06T14:32:00-05:00" n="272" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d272">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/3237</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_ORJD1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">O’Rear</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-06T15:00:00-04:32">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1917, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.45 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Note received from Bolivian Government announces that it is
                                thoroughly in accord with view of the Government of the United <pb facs="0395" n="223" xml:id="pg_223"/> States on Germany’s
                                submarine policy but declares it has not been notified by German
                                Government. As soon as it is advised by Germany, will immediately
                                notify me of policy adopted by Bolivia.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_ORJD1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">O’Rear</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>